. Why do we use the this keyword?

We use the this keyword to refer to the current object of the class. It is mainly used to resolve the ambiguity between instance variables and local variables
(or constructor parameters) when they have the same name. It is also used for constructor chaining, calling current class methods, passing the 
current object, and returning the current object.

