Interview Questions
Q1. What is a static variable?
Answer:
A static variable belongs to the class. Only one copy is created and shared among all objects.

Q2. Why do we use static variables?
To save memory when a value is common to all objects.

Example:
College Name
Company Name
Bank Name
PI Value
Q3. What is a static method?
A method that belongs to the class and can be called without creating an object.

Q4. Why can't a static method directly access instance variables?
Because instance variables belong to objects, and a static method belongs to the class. Without an object, Java doesn't know which instance variable to use.

Q5. Why is main() static?
Because the JVM calls main() without creating an object.

Q6. What is a static block?
A static block is executed once when the class is loaded into memory, before main().
